Body: We are using the Ethereum network for now. While we are working on our private blockchain to solve scalability issues. There is no virtual minders in Flashmoni but only real ones as we have invested in real gold mines. OZT value is based on the amount of gold you own but you do not own any gold yet, which you are going to buy/mint with part of the funds collected. But still, the amount of OZT circulated would be much higher than the gold you own. Therefore, I would like to know if my hard earned investment in a sound business? We have created two types of tokens. OZG and OZT. OZG is the digital representation of the gold Quantum Quorum (Flashmoni Global Custodian) will own. OZT=security token. And the OZT is the utility token to use Flashmoni Ecosystem valued 1/20 of OZG Token. In addition, founders have a strong knowledge of the yellow metal. All those 730 millions of tokens will be backed with 2300 kg of gold. We do not need to prove that the gold will be available on ICO completion because a third auditor party will be responsible for the reviewing the respective amount on a monthly basis.

Title: [ANN][ICO] FLASHMONI - Blockchain-powered Fintech 2.0
Body: Flashmoni created two types of tokens namely OZG and OZT ( the first one for a private tokenbacked with physical gold called. The later one on is a public token). Based on the Ethereum and Blockchain, it will be used within the FLASHMONI ecosystem. The value of one OZT is onetwentieth (1/20) of the value of the OZG. Each OZG token is backed by one grain of gold (i.e. 1 grain of gold = 1 OZG). You would need 480 grains of gold to have one ounce of 24-karat gold. We set the core value of our utility token (OZT) at $0.137. Of course, its value will increase according to the bid and ask market’s mechanism. The people who will participate in our ICO will have a limited chance to see the core value of our token fall one day after being on the market simply because it’s based on something real.

Author: flashmoniltd
Title: [ANN][ICO] FLASHMONI - Blockchain-powered Fintech 2.0
Body: An All-In-One Smart Card That Securely Bridges the Real and Digital Worlds Credit and debit card designers and engineers have been working over the years to make the use of cards safer. The introduction of the EMV chip technology in cards is about the latest widespread effort to take card safety to the next level. Put simply, an EMV card, or a chip-andPIN card, has a unique computer chip that stores the account data of the card. During a transaction, unlike in the traditional magnetic-stripe card, the chip creates a unique, one-time transaction code, which, as the description suggests, cannot be reused. This helps to prevent card counterfeiting.

Body: Why there are two types of tokens? For what?

Author: flashmoniltd
Title: [ANN][ICO] FLASHMONI - Blockchain-powered Fintech 2.0
Body: Please take note that Flashmoni created two types of tokens namely OZG and OZT ( the first one for a private token backed with physical gold called. The later one on is a public token). Based on the Ethereum and Blockchain, it will be used within the FLASHMONI ecosystem. The value of one OZT is onetwentieth (1/20) of the value of the OZG. Each OZG token is backed by one grain of gold (i.e. 1 grain of gold = 1 OZG). You would need 480 grains of gold to have one ounce of 24-karat gold. We set the core value of our utility token (OZT) at $0.137. Of course, its value will change according to the bid and ask market’s mechanism.

Author: flashmoniltd
Title: [ANN][ICO] FLASHMONI - Blockchain-powered Fintech 2.0
Body: During a transaction, unlike in the traditional magnetic-stripe card, the chip creates a unique, one-time transaction code, which, as the description suggests, cannot be reused. This helps to prevent card counterfeiting.

Author: flashmoniltd
Title: [ANN][ICO] FLASHMONI - Blockchain-powered Fintech 2.0
Body: Hello. The website works correctly. You have to do the follow steps: 1. Log in or sign up for an account – you will be re-directed to Flashmoni’s wallet at https://app.flashmoni.io 2. Once signed up, open a new page on your web browser to access MyEtherWallet site to create an Ethereum (ETH) wallet Please note: • Flashmoni ONLY accepts ETH contributions with ERC-20 compatible wallets • Flashmoni does NOT accept wallets from exchangers such as Poloniex or Jaxx 4. Follow the steps indicated on MyEtherWallet site and SAVE YOUR PRIVATE KEY and your WALLET information Please note: • MyEtherWallet only shows it once and you’ll need it to access your e-wallet account. 5. Fill your new MyEtherWallet with the amount of ETH you will be using to obtain OZTs during the Flashmoni’s Crowdsale 6. Now go back to the Flashmoni’s e-wallet, click on the “contribute” button and copy the Flashmoni’s ETH wallet account address 7. Go back to your MyEtherWallet and paste Flashmoni’s ETH wallet account address, and introduce the amount of ETH you’re going to contribute for the Crowdsale. Check Flashmoni’s site and the Ambassador Program to know the quantity of OZTs you are able to have during pre-sale, pre-ICO and ICO, and CLICK ON SEND 8. Once transfer to Flashmoni is completed, please send us the confirmation to finance@flashmoni.io. Your OZTs will be deposited in your Flashmoni’s e-wallet within 48 hours.

Title: [ANN][ICO] FLASHMONI - Blockchain-powered Fintech 2.0
Body: According to World Bank’s “Universal Financial Access” (UFA 2020), two billion people don’t have proper financial services. Author: flashmoniltd
Title: [ANN][ICO] FLASHMONI - Blockchain-powered Fintech 2.0
Body: An All-In-One Smart Card That Securely Bridges the Real and Digital Worlds Credit and debit card designers and engineers have been working over the years to make the use of cards safer. The introduction of the EMV chip technology in cards is about the latest widespread effort to take card safety to the next level. Put simply, an EMV card, or a chip-andPIN card, has a unique computer chip that stores the account data of the card. During a transaction, unlike in the traditional magnetic-stripe card, the chip creates a unique, one-time transaction code, which, as the description suggests, cannot be reused. This helps to prevent card counterfeiting.
